	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Durban – Three armed men robbed a restaurant at a service station in Mount Edgecombe on Tuesday, KwaZulu-Natal police said. Around 13:00, they held staff at gunpoint and demanded cash, police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said. They fled in a car with an undisclosed amount of cash. No shots were fired and nobody was hurt. A case of business robbery was opened at the Phoenix police station. No arrests had been made yet. On Monday, three men were shot dead and a fourth was injured in a botched cash heist in Hillcrest. The four tried to raid a cash van which had stopped at a petrol station to collect money.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  